**Hal Finney** was the recipient of the first bitcoin [[transaction]].

## Death

Hal Finney was diagnosed with Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS) in August 2009. (2.1) His bitcoins (which he mined in early 2009) were spent on medical bills as his ALS progressed in 2013. (2.2) He made arrangements with Alcor Life Extension Foundation to be cryopreserved upon being declared legally dead. (2.3)

Hal died and was cryopreserved on August 28, 2014. (2.2)

